<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<!--
  Fast DDS scaling profile. The dominant large-node-count failure mode is the
  default mutation_tries=100: once a host has ~100 participants, new ones can no
  longer claim a unique unicast listening port and silently go "deaf"
  (eProsima/Fast-DDS#6383, which #5767 dedups to). In ROS 2 Release builds the
  warning is compiled out, so the failure is invisible. Raising mutation_tries
  to 1000 is the maintainers' recommended mitigation; it lets participants keep
  probing for a free port. Applied to every participant via
  FASTDDS_DEFAULT_PROFILES_FILE + RMW_FASTRTPS_USE_QOS_FROM_XML=1.

  Discovery stays simple (SPDP). A Discovery Server was tried to get past the
  ~119-participants/host port-collision ceiling, but it collapses when many
  nodes start at once (#6383) and brought up 0/200, worse than simple discovery,
  so it was dropped (see rmw_matrix.py). At 200 simultaneous participants on one
  host, simple discovery is itself slow (an O(N^2) storm) -- a real Fast DDS
  limitation, not something this profile can tune away.
-->
<dds xmlns="http://www.eprosima.com">
    <profiles>
        <participant profile_name="bench_participant" is_default_profile="true">
            <rtps>
                <builtin>
                    <mutation_tries>1000</mutation_tries>
                </builtin>
            </rtps>
        </participant>
    </profiles>
</dds>
